I knew that a Chicago Dog or Italian-style dog was going to be a must have for me on my trip. I decided to come here for a late night bite and found the store was mostly empty. I got an Italian Dog with a side of fries and was satisfied with my order. The Italian Dog was new to me, but had a nice flavor. The meat was cooked well and felt like quality meat. The pickle garnishments were a nice touch and added crunch. I didn't even add condiments to my dog and enjoyed it. The fries were nice, thick steak fries with crunch.  Overall, the restaurant was very clean and service was good. It did not take long to get my order. For the price point of $5 a dog, it's okay for the value. This is a good place to stop by for a quick bite at night or to get some hot dogs.

I was the only customer when I came in. The cashier was sitting down playing on his phone. I had to greet him twice before he acknowledged me. I ordered the 1/3 cheesebuger meal. As I sat down, I noticed all the tables had crumbs on them. When my food was ready, I picked it up from the counter and noticed that A) the beef patty was WAY smaller than 1/3lb. and B) noticeably burned.  I tried to salvage the burger with some ketchup, but as I opened it I saw the lettuce leaf was completely white. It looked like a piece of toilet paper. I placed it on a napkin, approached the counter, displayed the toilet paper lettuce, and asked if they had any green lettuce. A panel discussion between employees ensued. After enough time for the burned burger and once-frozen fries to get cold, I was offered a few leaves of somewhat greenish lettuce.  I see that this establishment is open until 3 AM. That implies they cater to drunks (it is on a bar street). That's good. I feel sorry for any sober customer who dares to venture inside.
